  "prompt": "What are the new features in iPhone 7?",
  "response": "The iPhone 7, released by Apple in September 2016, introduced several new features and improvements over its predecessor, the iPhone 6S. Here are the key new features:\n\n1. **Design and Build**:\n   - **Water and Dust Resistance**: The iPhone 7 has an IP67 rating, meaning it is resistant to dust and can withstand being submerged in up to 1 meter of water for 30 minutes.\n   - **New Color Options**: The iPhone 7 introduced new color options, including Jet Black and Matte Black, in addition to the traditional Silver, Gold, and Rose Gold.\n\n2. **Display**:\n   - **Wide Color Gamut**: The Retina HD display supports a wider color gamut, offering more vibrant and true-to-life colors.\n   - **3D Touch**: Continued support for 3D Touch, which allows for pressure-sensitive interactions with the display.\n\n3. **Processor**:\n   - **A10 Fusion Chip**: The iPhone 7 is powered by the A10 Fusion chip, which is faster and more efficient than the A9 chip in the iPhone 6S. The A10 Fusion chip features a quad-core design with two high-performance cores and two high-efficiency cores.\n\n4. **Camera**:\n   - **Improved Rear Camera**: The 12-megapixel rear camera has a larger aperture (\u0192/1.8) for better low-light performance, optical image stabilization (on the iPhone 7 Plus model), and a six-element lens.\n   - **7-Megapixel Front Camera**: The front-facing camera is upgraded to 7 megapixels, with better image quality and features like Retina Flash for improved low-light selfies.\n   - **Dual-Lens Camera on iPhone 7 Plus**: The iPhone 7 Plus features a dual-lens camera system with a 12-megapixel wide-angle lens and a 12-megapixel telephoto lens, enabling 2x optical zoom and portrait mode with bokeh effect.\n\n5. **Audio**:\n   - **Stereo Speakers**: The iPhone 7 includes stereo speakers, with one speaker at the bottom and another at the top, providing a better audio experience.\n   - **Removal of the Headphone Jack**: Apple removed the traditional 3.5mm headphone jack, transitioning to a Lightning port for audio and introducing the AirPods as a wireless alternative.\n\n6. **Home Button**:\n   - **Solid-State Home Button**: The home button is no longer a physical button but a solid-state, pressure-sensitive button with haptic feedback provided by the Taptic Engine.\n\n7. **Storage Options**:\n   - **Increased Base Storage**: The base storage option was doubled from 16GB to 32GB, with additional options of 128GB and 256GB.\n\n8. **Battery Life**:\n   - **Improved Battery Life**: The iPhone 7 offers longer battery life compared to the iPhone 6S, with up to 2 additional hours of use.\n\n9. **iOS 10**:\n   - The iPhone 7 launched with iOS 10, which introduced new features like a redesigned lock screen, improved Siri, and a more interactive Messages app.\n\nThese features collectively made the iPhone 7 a significant upgrade, offering better performance, improved camera capabilities, and enhanced durability.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
